The Western Cape is still the epicentre with the country's highest death toll. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has seen an increase in COVID-19 cases in a day. The latest number of infections soared to 13,524. Nine new deaths have also been recorded taking the toll to 247. READ: Increase in local COVID-19 cases, death toll So far, 421,555 tests have been conducted. The number of recoveries stands at 6,083. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.